I spoke with the @UticaOD about my plans for a second term. Here’s just a few highlights of how I’ll help Upstate and America:  ✅ Deliver COVID relief 🥊 Hold Spectrum accountable 🇺🇸 Heal our divisions  #NY22 if we work together we can get it done!  https://t.co/dXvdoinyGn

#NY22 as I told the Rome Sentinel editorial board our small cities counties and towns need assistance. We cannot wait as COVID and the economic crisis threaten to destroy our communities.  Read more here: https://t.co/uSioBeqCYK

#Binghamton is distributing $1 million in COVID federal relief funds granted by the CARES Act! Residents call 211 now if you need assistance with your utilities rent or mortgage.  #NY22 I am fighting to get us more help Washington needs to step up!  https://t.co/QV4Eir3b5Y
The initial plan of the Coronavirus Food Assistance Program (CFAP) did not provide enough support for New York’s producers. We fixed that. Now we’re fighting for more.  https://t.co/CgspcczMLU

ICYMI I wrote an op-ed blowing the whistle on Spectrum’s plan to cap your Internet data. Their greed is unacceptable even more so during the coronavirus crisis when so many have had to cut back. #NY22 we must fight this.  https://t.co/GkiMHrbZvD

Our #NY22 farmers are the backbone of our country’s economy and food security. Like so many of our small businesses and workers they have been greatly hurt by the coronavirus pandemic.   Washington needs to put politics aside and get Americans the help they need! https://t.co/uxHV7CsqDQ
The House worked to solve this very problem in the recent bipartisan coronavirus relief bill I supported but if the FCC says it is ‘OK’ for Spectrum now we’re all in trouble.
This year’s number one back-to-school supply is the internet itself. Many local parents — and their kids — will require the internet this fall as part of schooling amid COVID-19.
#NY22 we’ve done a great job fighting the coronavirus and we need to continue to keep these numbers down. Do your part make sure to always wash your hands and stop the spread! https://t.co/kL1pSdDC83

Our Mohawk Valley businesses have this flexibility and entrepreneurial spirit. Very happy to see NY State supporting our community’s hard work with grants to make PPE and fight #COVID19. Keep up the good work #NY22!   PS #MaskUpUpstate 😷
It is imperative that both parties work together to fight back against COVID and get our economy moving. Getting help for you is my number one priority.  #NY22
Dan Casler is a 9th generation farmer here in the Mohawk Valley. His family farm like so many in our region has been hit hard by the COVID pandemic. https://t.co/dIQieFN3Yc

Why are supplies from China needed in a coronavirus fight? I’m determined to change that.  I introduced the "Made In America Emergency Preparedness Act" to strengthen our supply chain so we aren't over-reliant on China and other countries to help us.  https://t.co/YNtIs6jc1k

Today we put politics aside to fight back against COVID-19 passing a bill in the House that provides:  ✅ Direct payments to hardworking Americans ✅ Relief for small businesses ✅ Access to health care services and broadband in rural areas  https://t.co/0hBpdcMdm8

Upstate NY is home to some of the best small businesses in the country but they’re hurting from recent COVID-19 safety measures.  If you or someone you know owns a small business check out the relief programs available: https://t.co/ylPRZMbw4W

@IanPickus @WAMCNews Fact: New York received $6.7 billion in Families First Coronavirus Act ($5.26 billion directly to state remainder to counties & NYC). Highest of any state $2 billion more than California. Plus hundreds of millions if not billions in funds to New York coming under Disaster Dec

I’m calling on President Trump to declare NY state a disaster area freeing up more federal money and resources to fight Coronavirus. I joined 14 members of Congress in sending a bi-partisan letter to the President emphasizing New York’s need for immediate help with COVID-19.

Last night President Trump signed into law our Families First Coronavirus Response Act bringing $33.7 million in emergency funding to our district. This is a big step in the right direction. There is so much more work left to do.

I have learned that last week I came in contact with another member of Congress who tested positive for COVID-19. Out of an abundance of caution and the recommendation of the Attending Physician of the United States Congress I will self quarantine until next Friday.
And if you’re able join me in supporting families in our area affected by COVID-19:  https://t.co/VkWgRmwyYS  https://t.co/DJh9gIWJSK  https://t.co/ZM0PQB3RAG

Tips to prevent the spread of COVID-19:  ✅ Wash hands for 20 seconds ✅ Self-distance ✅ Disinfect all hard surfaces ✅ Cover your mouth w/ a tissue when you cough ✅ Know the symptoms - cough fever difficulty breathing? Isolate and call your doctor  We’re in this together.
